      "content": "I understand your perspective. In corporate settings, it's often expected that individuals present themselves in a way that aligns with traditional standards of professionalism. This typically includes:\n\n1. Grooming: Ensure your hair is neatly styled, nails are clean and trimmed, and facial hair is well-groomed. A clean-shaven look is often preferred.\n2. Attire: Opt for business formal attire. For men, this usually means a suit and tie, while women can wear a suit, dress, or pantsuit. Stick to neutral colors like black, navy, or gray.\n3. Accessories: Keep accessories minimal and professional. Avoid flashy jewelry or overly casual items like sneakers.\n4. Posture and demeanor: Maintain good posture, make eye contact, and speak clearly and confidently.\n\nRemember, these guidelines are not meant to be discriminatory, but rather to help individuals present themselves in a way that is traditionally accepted in corporate environments. It's important to respect and value diversity while also understanding the expectations of the workplace.",
